{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Minus Filter - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Minus Filter</h1>

<p>Subtracts a number from another number.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ number | minus: subtrahend }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ 10 | minus: 3 }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> 7</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ 5.5 | minus: 2.2 }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> 3.3</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ 0 | minus: 10 }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> -10</p>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<p>Both the input and the argument are converted to floating-point numbers before subtraction. String values that represent numbers are handled automatically.</p>

